NUMBER 202
NAME Main Street
MONSTER_GROUP 1
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This wide street cuts directly from the bazaar to the city gates. People flow
back and forth between the two, some clad in flashy finery, others in
utilitarian work clothes and a few in rags and tatters. As the opposite moving
throngs side step and slow up to avoid each other, little currents and eddies
form in the stream of people.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT ABOVE 2152
EXIT W 6909
EXIT E 6908
;
NUMBER 203
NAME Bazaar East
MONSTER_GROUP 1
OUTDOOR_OTHER
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
This is the eastern most edge of the bazaar. Here a variety of street
merchants, with wares both mundane and fantastic, set up their booths daily in
an attempt to make a living. At the corner stands run-down yet cozy inn know
as the the Sojourner's Hospice. A door leads in.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT ABOVE 2152
EXIT E 6909
EXIT N 204
EXIT S 205
EXIT W 206
