NUMBER 242
NAME Church Street
FIXED_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
A whitewashed wooden building houses the Church of Shemri. You can see its
quaint steeple for some distance. Within is a bell for announcing weddings
and other occasions. On the opposite side of the street, through a stone
arch, is a shrine to Amilor.  A wooden door, flower-decked, leads into
the Church of Shemri.
*DESCRIPTION_END
