*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
You see the stately two-story red brick townhouse of Cyrano de Bergerac,
Former High Lord of the Crimson Band and Ambassador of King Kentaurus III
to Shamradur. The intricately molded wrought iron gate surrounds the
residence and the carefully tended English garden located within. The garden
is dominated by a half-dozen giant elm trees, providing a picturesque front
yard. The fence gate is supported by two sturdy basalt stone pillars with
grinning gargoyle heads carved atop each.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The short black-stained iron fence surrounding the townhouse was designed more for decoration than defense. The gate itself, supported by the stone pillars, is well oiled and beckons you inside.
*DESCRIPTION_END
