Number 6915
Name O'Berin Way
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
O'Berin's Way leads off from the Bazaar where quaint homes closely hug
the narrow cobblestoned street. Passersby stroll along, admiring the
ornate trim and colorful awnings of the windows and doorways. Except
for a few flowerboxes, the street is devoid of all shrubbery.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 204
EXIT N 6916
;
Number 6916
Name O'Berin Way
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The picturesque street narrows to little more than a pathway. Pidgeons
roost on the rooftops and the sun shines little on this part of the
street. One can hear the occasional sound of children's laughter as
they dart in and out of the alleyways between the houses.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 6917
EXIT S 6915
;
Number 6917
Name O'Berin Way
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The road widens slightly here and the light bursts through as you come
Atop the lamp sits a decorative ornament of an eagle with it's wings
spread. As you glance up at the eagle, it seems to stare back at you
with guarding eyes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 6918
EXIT S 6916
