Number 6918
Name Windrunner Street
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Just east of O'Berin's Way onto tree-lined Windrunner Street, you see
modest homes with small front yards, each separated by picket fences.
Neighbors occasionally gather to relax and gossip on their porches in a
pleasant friendly atmosphere. Lush trees offer shade and shelter to the
birds and squirrels that run from limb to limb. A small, shingled bungalow
is nestled neatly on the north side of the street.
*DESCRIPTION_END
