Number 6922
Name WIndrunner Street
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The street comes to an end forming a cul-de-sac. The fences are adorned
with creeping rose bushes of reds and pinks. You notice a small copse
of trees back from the road and a trail winding down a small
hill allowing just a glimpse of a cottage slightly away from the other
homes.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT W 6921
;
Number 6923
Name Thinvar Avenue
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
North from Windrunner Street is the posh Thinvan Ave. Here the homes are
farther apart and more ornate. The greenery is more dense and surrounding
the houses are neatly trimmed and well-cared for lawns. This quiet
neighborhood seems ideal for peaceful living.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 6920
EXIT N 6924
;
Number 6924
Name Thinvar Avenue
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Mighty trees are seen up and down the street, some shading the steep roofs
and others standing proud at the side of road. Occasionally you see
birdhouses and feeders drawing many different varieties of birds. Their
chirping is sometimes the only sound you hear.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 6923
EXIT N 6925
;
Number 6925
Name Thinvar Avenue
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Here you see a high wall put together by stone of many sizes and shapes.
The wall contains a wrought iron gate that really reveals nothing as one
tries to peek through, except thick foliage and vines. A small area of
mostly pine trees is noticable on the other side of the road where a carpet
of needles form a path leading away from the street.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 6924
EXIT N 6926
