NUMBER 6935
NAME Main Street
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tall buildings stand shoulder-to-shoulder here, nearly blocking out the
sky above. Few signs indicate what sort of business is conducted inside.
A few traders pass in and out of the doors, but no other foot-traffic
gives you any clue as to the nature of these buildings.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 209
EXIT W 254
;
NUMBER 6936
NAME Main Street
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
The tall buildings are interrupted momentarily on this part of Main. A
tiny park has been created here for weary travellers and shoppers to take
a breath of fresh air and rest a bit. Weathered, wooden benches sit
beneath thick, hanging oaks and a tiny path meanders through a small
garden of roses and hydrangeas. Several children play and wrestle on the
soft, green grass while their parents sit by watchfully, resting up before
continuing on their way.
*DESCRIPTION_END
