NUMBER 6938
NAME Main Street
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Older buildings, with more character, line either side of main street.
Most of the buildings are made of crumbling brick with stone gargoyles
peering down at you from the roof-tops. Reading a couple of signs, you
realize that most of these stores deal with the mystical arts. One
shop sells books on magic and the occult, while its neighbor sells items
to ward off evil and demons. One of the shops across the street seems
to be in the business of protecting Fayd's citizenry from the undead.
*DESCRIPTION_END
