Number 6940
Name Broadway
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
A tall, dilapitated house, home to the Rat Catcher's Guild, stands alone on
this part of the street. Tall piles of wood and rubble are testament to the
homes that used to be here. Outside the guild hall, several unsavory people
carrying burlap bags stained with blood, loiter near the door, waiting to
trade their fly-infested burdens for a few coins.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 229
EXIT W 230
;
Number 6941
Name Broadway
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The main building on this part of the street is home to a soup kitchen run
in alliance by several of the churches in the city to help feed the poor and
down-trodden. A small line of shabbily dressed people stand outside the
kitchen at all times, waiting for a hot, decent meal.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 240
EXIT W 6942
;
Number 6942
Name Broadway
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tucked in amongst small, shabby homes is the guild hall for the Lantern
Lighters of Fayd. A group of young men and women sit around the outside
of the hall talking and trading jokes during the daylight hours. A strong
odor of lantern oil wafts out from the building as someone opens the door
to enter the hall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 6941
