Name Deepwood Avenue
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
Towering pine trees line the street and dusty cobwebs cover many of the vines which grow upon the stone walls on either side of Deepwood Avenue. Massive houses can barely be seen behind the walls and trees. A large bluejay has taken up residence in t
his section of the neighborhood and you see it dive at other birds as it seeks to protect it's territory. Deepwood Avenue continues to the east and west.
*DESCRIPTION_END
