NUMBER 7029
NAME Manor Row
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
A great brick arch towers above you at the beginning of Manor Row. Looking
above you see that fragrant blossoms and drooping vines have found purchace
in cracks and crevices in the ancient bricks. The wide, cobblestoned avenue
is shaded by the sprawling branches of tall oaks and lazy willows. The silent
sentinels seem to stand watch over the elegant homes of minor nobles and
wealthy merchants that live in this neighborhood. To the north is Deepwood
Avenue, to the south Manor Row continues through the shade trees.
*DESCRIPTION_END
