NUMBER 7030
NAME Manor Row
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
On the west side of the avenue the tree-shrouded homes continue uninterrupted
and to the east, the cobble-stoned road branches off to Darkwood Road.
Looking south, you catch brief glimpses, over rooftops and through branches,
of the towers and parapets of the Royal Palace. As you continue along, you
trade nods of greetings with servants burdened with bags and packages.
*DESCRIPTION_END
