NUMBER 7031
NAME Manor Row
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Manor Row continues showcasing the beautiful homes of the rich and titled. It
appears that each home-owner is trying to outdo their neighbor in displaying
his or her wealth to the passing traffic. One home on the east side of the
avenue has a gigantic garden filled with every kind and color of rose
imaginable, planted and pruned to grow into a magnificent representation of
their family crest. Pulling your gaze from the floral display, your eyes
light upon a huge gathering of every race and creature imaginable. It would
appear that one of the home owners has a love of sculpture and the brightly
painted figures rival even the brightest of gardens.
*DESCRIPTION_END
