Number 7040
Name Hardwood Avenue
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The city's western wall towers above you causing Hardwood Avenue to come to
an abrupt end here. The residents of the neighborhood have taken advantage
of this fact by placing a large statue in the center of the road, just before
the wall. The statue commemorates those who died in the War of 785 which
brought King Fredrick the first to power. Many of the current nobles are
descended from these heros, as evidenced by the many freshly cut flowers
placed at the base of the statue. To the east, Hardwood Avenue continues and
to the west, the city wall blocks further progress.
*DESCRIPTION_END
