NUMBER 7041
NAME Hardwood Avenue
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
Many nobles of the Royal Court make their home here. Large iron gates and
brick walls seperate the immaculate estates from the yellow brick avenue
upon which you travel. Personal guards, each wearing colors of the various
noble houses, watch you closely from behind the gates.
To the east, the estates along the avenue continue and to the west, you see
a large statue beofre the city wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT E 7042
EXIT W 7040
