NUMBER 7049
NAME Broadway
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_OTHER
*DESCRIPTION_START
The largely empty halls of the Royal Academy of Scribing and Counting stand
testament to the philanthropic attitudes of King Frederic I. A few of the
more enthusiastic scholars sit on the wide, stone steps of the building,
vigorously practicing their lessons.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 227
EXIT S 228
